<para id="fs-idm28348160"><emphasis effect="italics">E. coli</emphasis> colonizes the surface of the leaf, forming a biofilm that is more difficult to remove than free (planktonic) cells. Additionally, bacteria can be taken up in the water that plants are grown in, thereby entering the plant tissues rather than simply residing on the leaf surface.</para>
